# Module Structure & Organization

## Module Categories

### Core Modules

- `app/`: Main application entry point
- `core/`: Common utilities, base classes, DTOs, exceptions
- `common/`: Shared utilities
- `security/`: Security configurations

### Feature Modules Pattern

Most feature modules follow the `-api` and `-core` separation:

- `{module}-api/`: Interfaces, DTOs, Entity definitions (no implementation)
- `{module}-core/`: Implementations, Controllers, Services, DAOs

Examples: `dict-api/dict-core`, `user-api/user-core`, `tenant-api/tenant-core`, `authorization-api/authorization-core`

### Standalone Modules

- `jwt-auth/`: JWT authentication
- `oauth-auth/`: OAuth authentication
- `oauth2-server/`: OAuth2 server
- `wechat-auth/`: WeChat authentication
- `captcha/`: Captcha module

## Package Naming Convention

- Base package: `com.vgerbot`
- Module packages: `com.vgerbot.{module}`
- Sub-packages: `controller`, `service`, `dao`, `entity`, `dto`, `config`, `exception`

## File Organization

```log
{module}/
├── build.gradle.kts
├── src/main/kotlin/com/vgerbot/{module}/
│   ├── controller/     # REST controllers
│   ├── service/        # Service interfaces/implementations
│   ├── dao/            # DAO interfaces/implementations
│   ├── entity/         # Ktorm entities and tables
│   ├── dto/            # Data transfer objects
│   ├── config/         # Configuration classes
│   └── exception/      # Custom exceptions
└── src/test/kotlin/    # Test files
```
